The spiral is the classic Ulam (counter‑clockwise) spiral  

\[
\begin{array}{c}
\ldots 5\;4\;3 \\
\ldots 6\;1\;2 \\
\ldots 7\;8\;9
\end{array}
\]

Give the centre \((0,0)\) the value \(1\); the \(x\)-axis points right,
the \(y\)-axis points up.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1.  Coordinates of a given number  

For a number \(n\)

* let \(m=\bigl\lceil\dfrac{\sqrt n-1}{2}\bigr\rceil\)  (the “layer’’);
* the side length of the square of that layer is \(2m+1\);
* the maximal number on the layer is \((2m+1)^2\) and lies at \((m,-m)\).

If \(\text{off}= (2m+1)^2-n\) then  

\[
(x,y)=
\begin{cases}
(m-\text{off},\; -m)                   & \text{if }\text{off}<2m,\\[4pt]
(-m,\; -m+(\text{off}-2m))            & \text{if }2m\le\text{off}<4m,\\[4pt]
(-m+(\text{off}-4m),\; m)             & \text{if }4m\le\text{off}<6m,\\[4pt]
(m,\; m-(\text{off}-6m))              & \text{if }6m\le\text{off}<8m .
\end{cases}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2.  Position of 2026  

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx 45.01,\qquad 
m=\Bigl\lceil\frac{45.01-1}{2}\Bigr\rceil =23 .
\]

\[
\text{off}=47^{2}-2026=2209-2026=183 .
\]

Since \(6m=138\) and \(183\ge 138\),

\[
x=m=23,\qquad y=m-(183-138)=23-45=-22 .
\]

Thus \(2026\) is at \((23,-22)\).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3.  Numbers of the eight neighbours  

For any lattice point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
L=\max(|x|,|y|),\qquad M=(2L+1)^2 .
\]

According to which side of the square \((x,y)\) lies on,

\[
\text{offset}= 
\begin{cases}
L-x                                          & y=-L,\\
2L+(y+L)                                     & x=-L,\\
4L+(x+L)                                     & y= L,\\
6L+(L-y)                                     & x= L .
\end{cases}
\]

The number there is \(M-\text{offset}\).

Applying this to the eight neighbours of \((23,-22)\):

| neighbour \((x,y)\) | \(L\) | side | offset | number |
|---------------------|------|------|--------|--------|
| \((22,-23)\) | 23 | bottom | \(23-22=1\) | \(2209-1=2208\) |
| \((23,-23)\) | 23 | bottom | \(23-23=0\) | \(2209\) |
| \((24,-23)\) | 24 | right  | \(6\cdot24+(24+23)=191\) | \(2401-191=2210\) |
| \((22,-22)\) | 22 | bottom | \(22-22=0\) | \(2025\) |
| \((24,-22)\) | 24 | right  | \(6\cdot24+(24+22)=190\) | \(2401-190=2211\) |
| \((22,-21)\) | 22 | right  | \(6\cdot22+(22+21)=175\) | \(2025-175=1850\) |
| \((23,-21)\) | 23 | right  | \(6\cdot23+(23+21)=182\) | \(2209-182=2027\) |
| \((24,-21)\) | 24 | right  | \(6\cdot24+(24+21)=189\) | \(2401-189=2212\) |

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum} &= 2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212\\
&= 16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
